This paper discusses the use of network analysis to map user interests in social media, which falls under the category of social media analysis. The paper specifically focuses on the social news website Reddit, which is a platform for sharing news and discussing topics of interest. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). 

The paper also discusses the network properties of the Reddit social network, which could fall under the categories of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of interest maps to help users navigate social media platforms, which could fall under the categories of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
